name: Luggage carrier
description: any accessory equipment designed to carry tools, gear or cargo

name: Rim
description: that part of a wheel to which the tire is attached and often forms part of the braking mechanism

name: Down tube
description: tube on the bicycle frame that runs from the head tube to the bottom bracket

name: Hub gear
description: a gearbox mounted inside the hub, 3-speed is common, 5, 7 are available and Rohloff make a 14-speed hub.

name: Bar ends
description: extensions at the end of straight handlebars to allow for multiple hand positions

name: Pedal
description: mechanical interface between foot and crank arm. There are two general types; one secures the foot.
